entity-family-annotation — validate/default the annotation entity families
==========================================================================

Status: DEFERRED (schms-parity 1.6.6). Parent: entity-mutation-parity.

The schms-parity pass registered and validated the 21 core entity
families (LINE .. XLINE, XRECORD) in
clautolisp/drawing/source/entity-families.lisp. The following
annotation families are NOT yet in the registry and are therefore
accepted PERMISSIVELY (pass-through, no required-code validation, no
subclass-marker / default stamping) by ENTMAKE / ENTMAKEX:

  - DIMENSION (all subtypes: rotated/aligned/angular/diametric/radial/
    ordinate; the anonymous *D block reference it owns)
  - LEADER, MLEADER, MULTILEADER (+ MLEADERSTYLE object)
  - TOLERANCE
  - MLINE (+ the MLINESTYLE object)
  - MTEXT advanced fields (the family IS registered with the minimal
    10/40/1 required set, but the column/inline-format/attachment codes
    — 71/72/73/44/45/46/48/49/50/63/90/101 — are neither validated nor
    defaulted)

Do
--

Add EntityFamily descriptors with the DXF-reference required codes and
subclass markers (AcDbDimension + per-subtype, AcDbLeader, AcDbMLeader,
AcDbFcf, AcDbMline), plus the associated *STYLE symbol-table / object
records where creation requires them. Add family + host lifecycle tests
and extend the portable probe (DIMENSION/MLINE need style + block
prerequisites — mirror the INSERT approach once entity-family-insert-
block-sequence lands).

Reference: AutoCAD DXF reference, ENTITIES section (DIMENSION, LEADER,
MLEADER, TOLERANCE, MLINE) and OBJECTS section (MLEADERSTYLE,
MLINESTYLE).
